      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SWEET KISSES (2) built on a near miss at Townsville with deserved success there over 1400m at this level. She's won 2/3 at this track, and at her only go here over this distance. Races handy and can go back-to-back. ARMOUR FORCE (6) drifted well back first-up before winding up strongly to just miss over 950m at this track. He's proven second-up and is sure to appreciate the longer sprint. Keeps Cormack, and he's right in it. Stablemate SMART LEGEND (3) will also race over further, but he deserves a betting watch first-up with Wiggins engaged. He's a well-performed galloper coming off tougher races and should be finishing on. ARCTIC BEAR (8) turned in a decent effort last start when he made late ground to miss by 1L over 950m at this track. Suitably placed at best, and the longer sprint will be an advantage.",
